<paragraph blockId="22.[2035,2629,2379,2805]" pageId="22" pageNumber="617">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2035,2190,2379,2412]" pageId="22" pageNumber="617">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
7 
<taxonomicName authority="Milne-Edwards, 1870" authorityName="Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1870" class="Mammalia" family="Talpidae" genus="Talpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="22" pageNumber="617" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longirostris">Talpa longirostris Milne-Edwards, 1870</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation pageId="22" pageNumber="617">Moupin (= Baoxing), Sichuan, China. Based on specimens from Vietnam, two new species,</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[2035,2629,2379,2805]" pageId="22" pageNumber="617">
E. kuznetsovi and E. orlovi, were separated from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1870" box="[2255,2426,2580,2609]" class="Mammalia" family="Talpidae" genus="Talpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="22" pageNumber="617" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longirostris">E. longirostris</taxonomicName>
, but taxonomic status of Chinese specimens has not yet been reevaluated. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
